text.section:
The Secretary shall adopt regulations governing the local department self-assessment process, including:
the development of quality assurance procedures;
performance standards;
the timing of the assessment;
the scope of the assessment;
the process by which the Administration may accept or reject the local assessment and the plan;
the process by which the Administration shall monitor the implementation of the local plans described in subsection (d) of this section; and
the process by which the Administration shall use the assessments of the local departments to develop the statewide assessment under Title 45 § 1355.33(b) of the Code of Federal Regulations.
